beforePayRecordedWith((address,address,(.details: Part of IJBFundingCycleDataSource.This implementation just sets this contract up to receive a `didPay` call.

params.context: The Juicebox standard network payment context. See

returns.hookSpecifications: Amount to be sent to pay hooks instead of adding to local balance. Useful for auto-routing funds from a treasury as payment come in.
returns.weight: The weight that network tokens should get minted relative to. This is useful for optionally customizing how many tokens are issued per payment.

params.controller: The controller that revnets are made from.
params.suckerRegistry: The registry that deploys and tracks each project's suckers.
params.trustedForwarder: The trusted forwarder for the ERC2771Context.

params.encodedConfiguration: A bytes representation of the revnet's configuration.
params.revnetId: The ID of the revnet having new suckers deployed.
params.suckerDeploymentConfiguration: The specifics about the suckers being deployed.

params.addr: The address to check if has permissions.
params.revnetId: The ID of the revnet to check permissions for.

returns._0: flag The flag indicating if the address has permissions to mint on the revnet's behalf.

isTrustedForwarder(address).details: Indicates whether any particular address is the trusted forwarder.

params.buybackHookConfiguration: Data used for setting up the buyback hook to use when determining the best price for new participants.
params.configuration: The data needed to deploy a basic revnet.
params.revnetId: The ID of the Juicebox project to turn into a revnet. Send 0 to deploy a new revnet.
params.suckerDeploymentConfiguration: Information about how this revnet relates to other's across chains.
params.terminalConfigurations: The terminals that the network uses to accept payments through.

beforePayRecordedWith((address,address,(.details: Part of IJBFundingCycleDataSource.This implementation just sets this contract up to receive a `didPay` call.

params.context: The Juicebox standard network payment context. See

returns.hookSpecifications: Amount to be sent to pay hooks instead of adding to local balance. Useful for auto-routing funds from a treasury as payment come in.
returns.weight: The weight that network tokens should get minted relative to. This is useful for optionally customizing how many tokens are issued per payment.

params.controller: The controller that revnets are made from.
params.suckerRegistry: The registry that deploys and tracks each project's suckers.

params.buybackHookConfiguration: Data used for setting up the buyback hook to use when determining the best price for new participants.
params.configuration: The data needed to deploy a basic revnet.
params.suckerDeploymentConfiguration: Information about how this revnet relates to other's across chains.
params.terminalConfigurations: The terminals that the network uses to accept payments through.

returns.revnetId: The ID of the newly created revnet.

params.encodedConfiguration: A bytes representation of the revnet's configuration.
params.revnetId: The ID of the revnet having new suckers deployed.
params.suckerDeploymentConfiguration: The specifics about the suckers being deployed.

params.addr: The address to check if has permissions.
params.revnetId: The ID of the revnet to check permissions for.

returns._0: flag The flag indicating if the address has permissions to mint on the revnet's behalf.

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.details: Make sure only mints can be received.

params.revnetId: The ID of the revnet to which the extensions apply.

returns._0: payHookSpecifications The pay hooks.

params.newOperator: The address of the new operator.
params.revnetId: The ID of the revnet having its operator replaced.

params.interfaceId: The ID of the interface to check for adherence to.

returns._0: A flag indicating if the provided interface ID is supported.

CONTROLLER().notice: The controller that networks are made from.

EXIT_DELAY().notice: The amount of time from a sucker being deployed to when it can facilitate exits.

SUCKER_REGISTRY().notice: The registry that deploys and tracks each project's suckers.

beforePayRecordedWith((address,address,(.notice: This function gets called when the revnet receives a payment.

beforeRedeemRecordedWith((address,addres.notice: This function is never called, it needs to be included to adhere to the interface.

buybackHookOf(uint256).notice: The data hook that returns the correct values for the buyback hook of each network.

deploySuckersFor(uint256,bytes,((address.notice: Allows a revnet's operator to deploy new suckers to the revnet after it's deployed.

exitDelayOf(uint256).notice: The time at which exits from a revnet become allowed.

payHookSpecificationsOf(uint256).notice: The pay hooks to include during payments to networks.

replaceOperatorOf(uint256,address).notice: A revnet's operator can replace itself.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Indicates if this contract adheres to the specified interface.

params.context: The Juicebox standard network payment context. See

returns.hookSpecifications: Amount to be sent to pay hooks instead of adding to local balance. Useful for auto-routing funds from a treasury as payment come in.
returns.weight: The weight that network tokens should get minted relative to. This is useful for optionally customizing how many tokens are issued per payment.

params.controller: The controller that revnets are made from.
params.suckerRegistry: The registry that deploys and tracks each project's suckers.
params.trustedForwarder: The trusted forwarder for the ERC2771Context.

params.encodedConfiguration: A bytes representation of the revnet's configuration.
params.revnetId: The ID of the revnet having new suckers deployed.
params.suckerDeploymentConfiguration: The specifics about the suckers being deployed.

params.addr: The address to check if has permissions.
params.revnetId: The ID of the revnet to check permissions for.

isTrustedForwarder(address).details: Indicates whether any particular address is the trusted forwarder.

params.buybackHookConfiguration: Data used for setting up the buyback hook to use when determining the best price for new participants.
params.configuration: The data needed to deploy a basic revnet.
params.revnetId: The ID of the Juicebox project to turn into a revnet. Send 0 to deploy a new revnet.
params.suckerDeploymentConfiguration: Information about how this revnet relates to other's across chains.
params.terminalConfigurations: The terminals that the network uses to accept payments through.

returns._0: revnetId The ID of the newly created revnet.

beforePayRecordedWith((address,address,(.details: Part of IJBFundingCycleDataSource.This implementation just sets this contract up to receive a `didPay` call.

params.context: The Juicebox standard network payment context. See

returns.hookSpecifications: Amount to be sent to pay hooks instead of adding to local balance. Useful for auto-routing funds from a treasury as payment come in.
returns.weight: The weight that network tokens should get minted relative to. This is useful for optionally customizing how many tokens are issued per payment.

params.controller: The controller that revnets are made from.
params.suckerRegistry: The registry that deploys and tracks each project's suckers.
params.trustedForwarder: The trusted forwarder for the ERC2771Context.

params.encodedConfiguration: A bytes representation of the revnet's configuration.
params.revnetId: The ID of the revnet having new suckers deployed.
params.suckerDeploymentConfiguration: The specifics about the suckers being deployed.

params.addr: The address to check if has permissions.
params.revnetId: The ID of the revnet to check permissions for.

returns._0: flag The flag indicating if the address has permissions to mint on the revnet's behalf.

isTrustedForwarder(address).details: Indicates whether any particular address is the trusted forwarder.

params.buybackHookConfiguration: Data used for setting up the buyback hook to use when determining the best price for new participants.
params.configuration: The data needed to deploy a basic revnet.
params.revnetId: The ID of the Juicebox project to turn into a revnet. Send 0 to deploy a new revnet.
params.suckerDeploymentConfiguration: Information about how this revnet relates to other's across chains.
params.terminalConfigurations: The terminals that the network uses to accept payments through.
